Originally this game seems fun and fresh. However after a few attempted playthroughs, it is anything but. The game brags about its lack of transactions...which is odd since the game feels and plays like a pay to win. It's nearly impossible with all but very few to drop the soap in showers. This knocks off a third of all your energy bars. One wrong shower trip and recovering is nearly impossible. Given how every action takes one hour, there just isn't enough time to do the right things without a guide. And then, what's the point? Either go pay to win, or take the pay to win aspect out of the game.

content: A great game. Take the time to learn how it works. I've been looking for game that involves fun character development and this is it * Choose your prisoner carefully and check the long term goal - make sure you achieve it to unlock better prisoners. Choose Rich and high Agility to help survive. Choose Basketball, Body building or Chess to join a gang straight away and do join a gang * Learn Basketball to give +6 survival in the showers * Bribe guards for favors * Develop Social and similar skills to make friends * Buy coffees and use instead of sleep and practice skills in your cell at night * Game saves at night sleep so you can go back to last save if you mess up in the day
